<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Beginner_LiveMode_AgingDeath" s="314259">
  <T n="name">0xA30AF022<!--String: "Aging & Death"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LiveMode\LiveMode_LifeStages_1.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:dc7e3f2e36b62fb6</T>
      <T n="text">0xB57E5530<!--String: "Follow your Sims from the cradle to the grave. As time goes on, Sims will <b><font color='#199C2C'>age</font></b> and go through seven <b><font color='#199C2C'>Life Stages</font></b>; <b><font color='#199C2C'>Baby</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Toddler</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Child</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Teenager</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Young Adult</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Adult</font></b>, and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Elder</font></b>.\n\nEach Life Stage offers unique <b><font color='#199C2C'>experiences</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>challenges</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_AgingAndDeath_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2415d18f2cb63892</T>
      <T n="text">0xFE231AA7<!--String: "Some Sims may have an <b><i><font color='#199C2C'>accident</font></i></b> before they reach the golden years of elderhood. \n\nBeware of fire, swimming while tired, and huge chunks of rock hurling towards you from the sky. Or you know, don’t, and see what happens!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_AgingAndDeath_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2415d18f2cb63893</T>
      <T n="text">0xAF4D1DC8<!--String: "You can modify the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Lifespan</font></b> of Sims, and which Sims age and which don’t. Open the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Game Menu</font></b>, select <b><font color='#199C2C'>Game Options</font></b>, and navigate to the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Gameplay</font></b> tab.\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Auto aging</font></b> is on by default for Played Sims; this includes your current <b><font color='#199C2C'>active Household</font></b> and other <b><font color='#199C2C'>Households</font></b> you have <b><font color='#199C2C'>played</font></b> previously. \n\nIf you want your active Household to age but not your other Households, you can select <b><font color='#199C2C'>Only Current Household</font></b> in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Auto Age (Played Sims)</font></b> setting."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
